= Code Blocks

Code blocks are used to display source code with syntax highlighting and formatting.

== Basic Code Block

[source]
----
function hello() {
  console.log("Hello, World!");
}
----

== Code Block with Language

[source,javascript]
----
function greet(name) {
  return `Hello, ${name}!`;
}

const message = greet("World");
console.log(message);
----

== Code Block with Title

[source,php]
.Title: Example PHP Code
----
<?php
class Example {
  public function hello() {
    return "Hello, World!";
  }
}
----

== Multiple Code Blocks

[source,python]
----
def fibonacci(n):
    if n <= 1:
        return n
    return fibonacci(n-1) + fibonacci(n-2)
----

[source,ruby]
----
def fibonacci(n)
  return n if n <= 1
  fibonacci(n-1) + fibonacci(n-2)
end
----

== Code Block with ID

[#my-code-block]
[source,javascript]
----
const example = "This code block has an ID";
----

